Kang Yong-Sop, a member of North Korea's Supreme  People's Assembly, or parliament, will attend a three-day religious conference  opening here May 31, a news report said Monday.
Kang, chairman of the central committee of the Korean Christians'  Federation and vice chairman of the Korea-Japan Friendship Association, is  expected to arrive in Tokyo on May 27, Kyodo News Service said.
A member of North Korea's Reunification Policy Committee, Kang has served  as ambassador to Romania.
